FBIS4-13501 "drnes077_n_94018" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 LEBANON Islamic Resistance Claims Attack on Israeli Patrol Islamic Resistance Claims Attack on Israeli Patrol NC2004200094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 20 Apr 94 NC2004200094 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] The Islamic Resistance has declared that the Martyr Muhammad Darwish Group launched a direct assault at 1830 today against an Israeli patrol composed of two personnel carriers, a Merkava tank, 13 infantry personnel, and a security vehicle on the 'Alman road, using various types of machine guns and rockets. A personnel carrier was burned out and its five crew members were killed or wounded and the security vehicle was hit. There were other casualties among the patrol personnel. Ambulances were seen rushing to the scene to evacuate the casualties. Agent Lahd's [South Lebanese Army] radio reported the operation and that one soldier was wounded.
